# Tim Sort

## Problem

Tim Sort is a hybrid sorting algorithm derived from Merge Sort and Insertion Sort.

It divides the array into small parts called runs, sorts them using Insertion Sort, and then merges them using Merge Sort.

It is used in Java and Python built-in sorting functions.

---

# Algorithm / Pseudo Code

BEGIN

INPUT array A
INPUT n

SET run = 32

// Sort small subarrays using Insertion Sort
FOR i = 0 TO n-1 STEP run

    APPLY Insertion Sort on A[i ... min(i+31, n-1)]

ENDFOR

// Merge sorted runs
FOR size = run TO n-1
    size = size * 2

    FOR left = 0 TO n-1 STEP 2*size

        mid = left + size - 1

        right = minimum(left + 2*size - 1, n-1)

        MERGE subarrays

    ENDFOR

ENDFOR

PRINT sorted array

END

